WEBVTT

00:00.068 --> 00:01.401
Previously on
<i>The Event.</i>

00:01.454 --> 00:03.042
I have no idea what it says.

00:03.043 --> 00:04.210
If he could read it,

00:04.278 --> 00:05.511
Dempsey knew more than
what he was telling you

00:05.579 --> 00:07.780
about why we're here
and about what happened.

00:07.848 --> 00:09.382
Our star has begun
to implode.

00:09.449 --> 00:11.217
We will bring
all of our people here

00:11.284 --> 00:12.479
and make this planet our own.

00:12.547 --> 00:14.537
She's doing what
she has to to save us.

00:14.605 --> 00:15.943
By committing genocide.

00:16.012 --> 00:17.243
We need to make room.

00:17.311 --> 00:19.546
The most efficient way
to spread the pathogen

00:19.614 --> 00:22.712
is by using three parallel
distribution channels.

00:22.780 --> 00:26.486
Within five weeks the vast
majority of the human population

00:26.554 --> 00:27.525
will be dead.

00:27.592 --> 00:28.764
I know about the virus.

00:28.832 --> 00:30.299
They used me
as a way to change it.

00:30.367 --> 00:31.535
I'm gonna get you
out of there.

00:31.603 --> 00:32.537
- You can't!
- What?

00:32.604 --> 00:33.879
I'm infected.

00:33.947 --> 00:35.881
Everything we need to know
about stopping the virus

00:35.949 --> 00:37.052
is on there.

00:37.119 --> 00:38.456
That's a lot of data
to sort through.

00:38.524 --> 00:39.793
The answer's right here.

00:39.860 --> 00:41.027
We're just gonna have to
figure it out on our own.

00:41.095 --> 00:42.095
The President is awake.

00:42.162 --> 00:43.497
Mr. President,
open your eyes, sir.

00:43.564 --> 00:45.533
Outstanding, sir. Yes.

00:45.600 --> 00:46.767
I know you tried to kill me.

00:46.835 --> 00:48.603
I am the President
of the United States.

00:48.671 --> 00:49.937
Not for long.

00:50.005 --> 00:51.305
There needs to be a vote
that you're capable.

00:51.373 --> 00:54.341
You can barely stand,
let alone lead this country.

00:54.409 --> 00:56.877
We just got word from home.
Our people are ready to come.

00:56.945 --> 00:58.612
Your job is to power
the array.

00:58.680 --> 01:00.314
Ready to activate
on your order.

01:00.382 --> 01:02.449
Proceed.

01:06.089 --> 01:08.224
Hey, Leila, stay with me.

01:08.292 --> 01:09.226
Leila.

01:09.293 --> 01:11.530
You have to stay awake, okay?

01:11.598 --> 01:14.034
Sterling called a specialist
at the CDC under the radar.

01:14.101 --> 01:16.505
He said they'll be here
any minute.

01:16.573 --> 01:17.507
Okay?

01:17.575 --> 01:19.209
It's too late for me.

01:19.276 --> 01:21.578
You have to worry about
everyone else.

01:21.646 --> 01:23.346
It's not too late.

01:23.414 --> 01:24.683
You can't think like that.

01:24.750 --> 01:28.386
Sean, I know what
this virus does.

01:28.454 --> 01:31.390
They said no one
can survive it.

01:31.458 --> 01:34.159
No. Simon said that
his people are immune to it.

01:34.227 --> 01:36.595
You share some of that DNA,
so...

01:36.662 --> 01:39.431
You have it within you
to fight this.

01:39.498 --> 01:43.568
Please...find Sam.

01:43.636 --> 01:46.471
Make sure she's okay.

01:46.539 --> 01:47.472
Leila.

01:47.540 --> 01:48.875
Hey. Stay with me.

01:48.943 --> 01:49.910
Leila.

01:49.978 --> 01:52.948
Leila!

01:53.015 --> 01:55.184
Oh, thank God.

01:55.252 --> 01:58.120
She's dehydrated,
she's very weak.

01:58.188 --> 01:59.622
How long has she been
symptomatic?

01:59.689 --> 02:02.091
Uh, I don't know, a day,
maybe two or three.

02:02.159 --> 02:05.529
Put her in a suit,
get her ready for transport.

02:05.597 --> 02:07.431
We're gonna take
good care of her.

02:07.499 --> 02:08.967
We need to get her
to a proper facility.

02:09.035 --> 02:10.134
And you need to leave the area.

02:10.203 --> 02:12.305
Okay.

02:12.372 --> 02:13.306
Leila?

02:13.374 --> 02:14.374
I'll find you, okay?

02:14.441 --> 02:15.742
It's gonna be fine.

02:15.810 --> 02:19.380
I'll be there.
Everything's gonna be okay.

02:19.448 --> 02:21.983
They built a model projecting
the spread of the disease

02:22.050 --> 02:23.618
over the next five weeks.

02:23.685 --> 02:25.019
Running the projection
backwards

02:25.087 --> 02:26.621
tells us where the attacks
will originate.

02:26.689 --> 02:30.225
By 5:30 today the pathogen
will have been released

02:30.293 --> 02:31.727
at these three locations:

02:31.795 --> 02:35.164
A food processing plant outside
of Richmond, Virginia;

02:35.231 --> 02:38.534
the U.S. Bureau
of Engraving in D.C.;

02:38.601 --> 02:41.603
and the international terminal
at Dulles Airport.

02:41.671 --> 02:43.071
Food, money, and travel.

02:43.139 --> 02:45.207
Within days it will be
everywhere.

02:45.275 --> 02:46.977
Do we know what kind of
delivery mechanisms

02:47.044 --> 02:47.978
they're using?

02:48.045 --> 02:49.446
Yeah. These.

02:49.513 --> 02:52.483
Pressurized aerosol
containers.

02:52.551 --> 02:54.485
We have to assume they're
either on their way

02:54.553 --> 02:57.856
or already in place
at the three locations.

03:02.696 --> 03:03.863
Teams one and two
are in place,

03:03.930 --> 03:05.431
prepping canisters
for release,

03:05.498 --> 03:06.632
no delays or disruptions.

03:06.700 --> 03:09.468
All right,
pull over here.

03:09.536 --> 03:11.137
Is there a problem?

03:11.205 --> 03:13.439
It'll be safer
if we're stopped.

